channel.title: Cache editor and rs2 map editor
channel.description:
For most people who don't know how to use google, I'm posting 2 useful tools for editing your standard 317/377. This was tested with "sea-scape", you can ask the creator of it if it works...
I did download the cache editor when it had a trojan, a keylogger and a RAT, I've taken out the trojan and I've nulled the rat, so this is absolutely safe... If you think otherwise, then please refer to these pictures that I've taken of scans for both my anti virus and anti spyware.
Cache editor: Download links: Short: http://up.ht/nnB3QX Original: http://uppit.com/qa2lztoo1pi7/cache_editor.zip
Virus and spyware scan:
Spyware scan: [IMG]http://i55.tinypic.com/302573m.jpg[/img]
Virus scan: [IMG]http://i51.tinypic.com/2r23jhf.jpg[/img]
The map editor: This only can do lumby based buildings. I'm not sure which file works, so test them out.
Spyware scan: [IMG]http://i52.tinypic.com/2z7e4it.jpg[/img]
Virus scan: [IMG]http://i54.tinypic.com/20utjxe.jpg[/img]
Downloads: short:http://up.ht/qOjWWT original: http://uppit.com/9io2a56yubl0/MapEditor.zip
Disclaimer:
I do not claim for any of these to be my work, I just simply made is safe to download both of them. They were cleared from a keylogger, a trojan and a RAT.
A picture of what my anti virus took out: http://prntscr.com/2wmmr
It's a screenshot taken by light screen or something.
If you think I must add credits then Here's a post of them:
Tom( the one who made the cache editor): 49% The person who made map editor: 49% Me: 2% for making the files safe.
